The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Sunday, October 31, 2004 

 Paris: World No. 1 Roger Federer of Switzerland will miss the upcoming Paris Masters tennis tournament after failing to shake off an injury, organisers said. Federer tore a muscle in his left thigh earlier this week during a warm up at the Swiss Indoors in Basel.

 With Federer out, American Andy Roddick went into Friday?s draw seeded No.1 for the $3.1 million indoor tournament in Paris? Bercy Stadium, which begins Monday.

 Meanwhile, 2003 French Open champion Juan Carlos Ferrero of Spain and Guillermo Coria of Argentina, the runner-up at Roland Garros this year, also pulled out. Ferrero did not give a reason for his absence, while Coria is still recovering from a shoulder operation, the French tennis federation said on its website on Friday.

 Mumbai: Rushmi Chakravarthi and Ankita Bhambri were the only Indians to be seeded at the $25,000 prize money MSLTA-ITF women?s tournament to be held at Dr Ranade Centre from Monday.

 Rushmi, who is ranked 337 in the world, and Ankita (417) are likely to be seeded fifth and seventh respectively, while Hana Sromova of Czech Republic, who is the highest ranked player at 237, will be seeded number one.

 Napaporn Tongsalee of Thailand (300), Gabriela Navratilova of Czech Republic (318), Akgul Amanmuradova of Uzbekistan (334), Montinee Tangphong of Thailand (351), Andreja Klepac of Slovakia (456), Sai Jayalakshmi (491) and Isha Lakhani (503) are the others well-known names who would be seen in action.

 Madrid: Atletico Madrid are considering a possible move from their centrally located stadium to a revamped stadium being planned as part of the capital?s Olympic bid. Deputy mayor Manuel Cobo told Radio Ser that he had held talks with the club over a possible switch, adding: ?The Olympic Committee does not want mausoleums hanging around after the Games are over. Madrid is one of five cities bidding to host the 2012 Olympics. 

 Lisbon: Porto midfielder Costinha left hospital on Friday after suffering a head injury in a Portuguese Cup match, the European champions said. The Portuguese international was caught on the head by Flavio Meireles? knee in the 2-1 defeat at Vitoria Guimaraes on Wednesday. The club said he would miss Porto?s next Champions League match at home to Paris St Germain on Tuesday. 

 Chandigarh: India registered a 4-1 victory over Pakistan in the first of the two-Test badminton series here this evening. The visitors were no match to their formidable opponents as the only point they scored was when the indians gave them a walkover in the second doubles after they had won the first three rubbers to take an unbeatable 3-0 lead. The hosts opened their campaign through hemant duggal, who posted an authoritative 15-4, 15-12 triumph over Wajid Ali in 45 minutes. 

 Cheste (Spain): Japan?s Makoto Tamada grabbed his third pole position of the season to take top spot for Sunday?s Valencia MotoGP after clocking the fastest time in the second qualifying session on Saturday. 

 Tamada?s Honda teammate Max Biaggi of Italy starts in second place and the front row will be completed by world champion Valentino Rossi.

